In his State of the Union Address, President Barack Obama congratulated the 112th Congress and emphasized the need for cooperation and unity in the face of challenges. He highlighted the importance of the American family and the shared hopes and dreams of its citizens. The President discussed the progress made in the economy and job creation, but acknowledged the need for further action to address long-term challenges. He emphasized the importance of innovation, education, and infrastructure in securing America's future. The President also touched on the topics of healthcare, immigration, and foreign policy, calling for comprehensive reform and continued American leadership. He concluded by reaffirming the American Dream and the ability of ordinary people to achieve extraordinary things.